org.lazywizard.lazylib.ui

Enum LazyFont.TextAnchor

  • Object
    • Enum<LazyFont.TextAnchor>
      • LazyFont.TextAnchor
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable, Comparable<LazyFont.TextAnchor>
    Enclosing class:
    LazyFont

    public static enum LazyFont.TextAnchor
extends Enum<LazyFont.TextAnchor>
    Represents the origin of drawing for LazyFont.DrawableStrings. For example, calling DrawableString#setAnchor(TextAnchor) with TOP_RIGHT would mean all calls to LazyFont.DrawableString.draw(float, float) will consider the top right of the LazyFont.DrawableString to be the origin when drawing, meaning all text would appear to the left and below the point passed into LazyFont.DrawableString.draw(float, float).
    Since:
    2.7
